#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/amortization_calculator.html:221
msgid "What is an Amortization Schedule?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/amortization_calculator.html:223
msgid ""
"An amortization schedule shows how each payment is split between principal "
"and interest over the life of the loan. Early payments are mostly interest; "
"later payments are mostly principal. This calculator generates a full "
"schedule and lets you add optional extra monthly payments to see how much "
"interest and time you can save."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/amortization_calculator.html:226
msgid "Monthly Payment = P × [r(1+r)^n] ÷ [(1+r)^n − 1]"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/amortization_calculator.html:227
msgid "P = principal, r = monthly rate, n = number of payments"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/amortization_calculator.html:229
msgid ""
"Interest for each period = balance × monthly rate. Principal = payment − "
"interest. New balance = previous balance − principal."
msgstr ""

