#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:211
msgid "What is an Annuity?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:212
msgid ""
"An annuity is a series of equal payments made at regular intervals (e.g., "
"monthly or annually). This calculator works with two types: ordinary "
"annuities (payments at the end of each period) and annuities due (payments "
"at the beginning of each period). You can find present value, future value, "
"or the payment amount needed given the other inputs."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:216
msgid "Present Value (PV)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:216
msgid ""
"The lump sum today that is equivalent to the stream of future payments, "
"given an interest rate."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:217
msgid "Future Value (FV)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:217
msgid ""
"The total value of all payments plus interest at the end of the last period."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:218
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_payout_calculator.html:216
msgid "Ordinary Annuity"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:218
msgid "Payments at the end of each period (e.g., most loans and mortgages)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/annuity_calculator.html:219
msgid ""
"Payments at the beginning of each period (e.g., rent, insurance premiums)."
msgstr ""

