#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:188
msgid "What is APR?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:190
msgid ""
"The interest rate is the cost of borrowing the principal. APR (Annual "
"Percentage Rate) includes the interest rate plus fees (origination, discount "
"points, and other closing costs), giving you the true yearly cost of the "
"loan. APR is always equal to or higher than the stated rate. Lenders are "
"required to disclose APR so you can compare offers."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:193
msgid ""
"APR reflects: (Interest + Fees) over the life of the loan, expressed as an "
"annual rate"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:194
msgid ""
"Net loan = Loan amount − Total fees. Payment is based on loan amount; APR is "
"solved so that payments match the net proceeds."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:202
msgid "Stated rate vs APR"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:203
msgid ""
"The stated (nominal) rate is the interest rate on the loan. APR includes "
"that rate plus upfront fees, so it represents the true cost of borrowing."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:206
msgid "Origination and fees"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:207
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Origination fee is a one-time charge (often a percentage of the loan). "
"Discount points (1 point = 1%% of loan) buy a lower rate. Other fees can "
"include processing or closing costs."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:210
msgid "Why compare APR?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:211
msgid ""
"A loan with a lower interest rate but high fees can have a higher APR. "
"Always compare APR when shopping; consider total cost and how long you will "
"keep the loan."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:219
msgid "Enter the loan amount, stated annual interest rate, and term in years."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:220
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Add origination fee (e.g. 1%% of loan), discount points (1 point = 1%% of "
"loan), and any other fees."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:221
msgid ""
"Click Calculate APR to see the true APR, monthly payment, total interest, "
"total fees, and fee breakdown."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:222
msgid "Review the cost breakdown chart and net loan amount."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:223
msgid "Use this to compare multiple loan offers before deciding."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:231
msgid "APR (hero)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:232
msgid ""
"The true annual cost of the loan including fees. This is the number to use "
"when comparing offers from different lenders."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:235
msgid "Monthly payment and total interest"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:236
msgid ""
"Based on the full loan amount and stated rate. Total interest is what you "
"pay in interest over the life of the loan."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:239
msgid "Fee breakdown and net loan"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:240
msgid ""
"Shows origination, points, and other fees. Net loan is the amount you "
"actually receive (loan amount minus total fees)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:248
msgid "Cost breakdown chart"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:249
msgid ""
"A doughnut or pie chart showing how much of the total cost is principal "
"(loan amount), interest, and fees. This helps you see the impact of fees at "
"a glance."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:258
msgid ""
"This calculator is for estimation. Actual APR may vary by lender and product."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:262
msgid ""
"Discount points are optional upfront fees that typically reduce your "
"interest rate; negotiate fees when possible."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/apr_calculator.html:266
msgid ""
"If you plan to refinance or move soon, paying points for a lower rate may "
"not be worth the upfront cost."
msgstr ""

