#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/average_return_calculator.html:327
msgid ""
"The average return can mean the simple (arithmetic) average of period "
"returns or the geometric average. The geometric average is the same as the "
"Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR): the constant yearly rate that would turn "
"your starting value into your ending value over the same period. CAGR "
"smooths volatility and is the standard way to compare investment performance "
"over time."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/average_return_calculator.html:333
msgid ""
"Use Start/End Values when you only know initial and final amounts; use "
"Annual Returns when you have year-by-year returns and want arithmetic mean, "
"geometric mean, standard deviation, and best/worst year."
