#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/canadian_mortgage_calculator.html:288
msgid "Semi-Annual Compounding"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/canadian_mortgage_calculator.html:291
msgid ""
"Unlike US mortgages which often compound monthly, Canadian mortgages "
"typically compound semi-annually (twice a year). This means the 'Effective "
"Annual Rate' (EAR) is slightly lower than if it were compounded monthly, "
"saving you money on interest."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/canadian_mortgage_calculator.html:297
msgid "Term vs. Amortization"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/canadian_mortgage_calculator.html:300
msgid ""
"The 'Amortization' is the total life of your loan (e.g., 25 years). The "
"'Term' is how long your rate is locked in (e.g., 5 years). You will renew "
"your mortgage multiple times over its life, potentially at different rates."
msgstr ""

