#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/debt_to_income_calculator.html:315
msgid ""
"Debt-to-Income (DTI) ratio is the percentage of your gross monthly income "
"that goes toward paying monthly debts. Lenders use it to assess your ability "
"to manage mortgage payments. A lower DTI generally improves your chances of "
"qualifying for a loan and may help you get better rates."
