#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:246
msgid "What is the Discount Calculator?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:248
#, python-format
msgid ""
"This calculator helps you work with discounts and sale prices. You can find "
"the sale price from an original price and a discount %%%%, find the discount "
"%%%% from original and sale price, find the original price from a sale price "
"and discount %%%%, or apply two discounts in a row (double discount). It "
"shows how much you pay, how much you save, and includes charts."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:255
#: Financial_Calculators/views/discount_calculator.py:103
#: Financial_Calculators/views/percent_off_calculator.py:116
msgid "Sale price"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:256
#, python-format
msgid ""
"What you pay after the discount. Sale price = Original price × (1 - "
"Discount%%%% / 100)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:260
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Discount amount = Original price - Sale price. The same as Original × "
"(Discount%%%% / 100)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:263
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/percent_off_calculator.html:57
msgid "Stacked discounts"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:264
#, python-format
msgid ""
"When you apply two discounts (e.g. 20%%%% off, then 10%%%% off), the second "
"is applied to the already-reduced price. The effective total discount is "
"less than 20%%%% + 10%%%%."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:271
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Choose: Sale Price (from original + %%%%), Discount %%%% (from two prices), "
"Original Price (from sale + %%%%), or Double Discount (two discounts in a "
"row)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:272
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Enter the known values. For Sale Price mode you can use the quick %% buttons."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:273
msgid "Click Calculate to see the result, breakdown, and charts."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:274
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Use the comparison chart to see sale prices at 10%%%%, 20%%%%, … 50%%%% off "
"for the same original price."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:280
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/percent_off_calculator.html:269
msgid "You Pay vs You Save:"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:280
msgid ""
"Doughnut chart showing the split between the amount you pay (sale price) and "
"the amount you save (discount)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:281
msgid "Sale Price at Different Discounts:"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:281
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Bar chart showing what the sale price would be at 10%%%%, 15%%%%, 20%%%%, "
"25%%%%, 30%%%%, 40%%%%, and 50%%%% off, based on your original price."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:287
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Discount percentage is between 0 and 100. For finding original from sale "
"price, use 0–99%%%% (100%%%% would mean free)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:288
#, python-format
msgid "Original price = Sale price ÷ (1 - Discount%%%% / 100)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/discount_calculator.html:289
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Double discount: first apply discount 1 to original, then apply discount 2 "
"to that result. Effective %%%% is always less than the sum of the two."
msgstr ""

