#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:219
msgid "What is a Down Payment?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:220
#, python-format
msgid ""
"A down payment is the portion of the home price you pay upfront in cash. It "
"reduces your loan amount and can lower your monthly payment and interest "
"cost. Conventional loans often require 5–20%%; 20%% or more typically avoids "
"Private Mortgage Insurance (PMI). FHA loans allow as little as 3.5%%."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:223
msgid "PMI and Closing Costs"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:226
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_calculator.html:460
msgid "PMI (Private Mortgage Insurance)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:227
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Required when you put less than 20%% down. It protects the lender and "
"typically costs 0.5–1%% of the loan amount per year until you reach 20%% "
"equity."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:231
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Fees for appraisal, title insurance, lender fees, etc. Usually 2–5%% of the "
"home price. Budget for them in addition to your down payment."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/down_payment_calculator.html:238
msgid "Enter the home price and your target down payment percentage."
msgstr ""

