msgid "What is the Federal Estate Tax?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/estate_tax_calculator.html:173
msgid ""
"The federal estate tax is a tax on the transfer of your estate at death. It "
"applies to the portion of your estate that exceeds the annual exemption "
"(about $13.61 million per person in 2024). Your gross estate includes real "
"estate, bank accounts, investments, retirement accounts, life insurance you "
"own, business interests, and other assets. Deductions (debts, expenses, "
"charitable bequests, and marital deduction) reduce the taxable amount. This "
"calculator estimates the federal tax and a rough state estimate; actual "
"results depend on your situation and state rules."
msgstr ""

