#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:301
msgid "What is Inflation?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:303
msgid ""
"Inflation is the rate at which the general level of prices for goods and "
"services rises over time, eroding purchasing power. It means that each unit "
"of currency buys fewer goods and services as time goes on. Inflation is "
"measured as an annual percentage increase."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:306
msgid "Future Value = Present Value × (1 + r)ⁿ"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:309
msgid ""
"Where r is the annual inflation rate (as a decimal) and n is the number of "
"years. This formula shows how much money you would need in the future to "
"have the same purchasing power as a given amount today."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:315
msgid "Inflation Categories"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:318
#, python-format
msgid "Deflation: Rate < 0%%"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:320
msgid ""
"Prices are falling. While consumers benefit short-term, prolonged deflation "
"can harm the economy by discouraging spending and investment."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:324
#, python-format
msgid "Low to Moderate: Rate 0%% - 4%%"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:326
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Healthy inflation range. Most central banks target around 2%% annual "
"inflation, which encourages spending and investment while keeping prices "
"relatively stable."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:330
#, python-format
msgid "High: Rate 4%% - 7%%"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:332
msgid ""
"Above-target inflation. Purchasing power erodes noticeably. Savings in low-"
"yield accounts lose real value. Consider inflation-protected investments."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:336
#, python-format
msgid "Very High: Rate 7%% - 10%%"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:338
msgid ""
"Significantly elevated inflation. Money loses value rapidly. Essential costs "
"increase substantially. Diversified investment strategies become critical."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:342
#, python-format
msgid "Extreme / Hyperinflation: Rate > 10%%"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/inflation_calculator.html:344
msgid ""
"Extremely high inflation that can destabilize economies. Historical examples "
"include Zimbabwe (2008) and Venezuela (2018+). Asset protection becomes "
"paramount."
msgstr ""

