#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:292
msgid "What is the Loan Calculator?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:294
msgid ""
"The Loan Calculator estimates your fixed monthly payment, total interest, "
"and payoff date for any amortizing loan (e.g. mortgage, auto, personal). "
"Enter the loan amount, annual interest rate, and term in years or months. "
"You can optionally add an extra monthly payment to see how much interest you "
"save and how many months earlier you pay off the loan."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:297
msgid ""
"Results include a payment breakdown chart (principal vs. interest), a "
"balance-over-time chart, and a full amortization schedule you can view by "
"month or by year. Use it to compare different rates, terms, or extra-payment "
"scenarios before you borrow."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:307
msgid ""
"The fixed amount due each period. It stays the same over the life of the "
"loan; only the split between principal and interest changes each month."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:313
msgid ""
"The total cost of borrowing over the life of the loan. Early payments are "
"mostly interest; reducing the rate, term, or adding extra principal lowers "
"this amount."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:319
msgid ""
"Principal plus total interest. This is the full amount you pay back to the "
"lender if you make every payment as scheduled (or with the extra amount you "
"entered)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:325
msgid ""
"The date the loan is fully paid. With extra payments, this date moves "
"earlier and you pay less total interest."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:334
msgid "Enter the loan amount (principal) you plan to borrow."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:335
msgid "Enter the annual interest rate and choose the term in years or months."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:336
msgid ""
"Optionally enter an extra monthly payment to see interest savings and "
"earlier payoff."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:337
msgid ""
"Click Calculate to see monthly payment, total interest, payoff date, payment "
"breakdown and balance charts, and the amortization schedule."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:338
msgid ""
"Switch between Monthly and Yearly views in the schedule to see per-period or "
"per-year totals."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:346
msgid "Monthly Payment and Total Payment"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:348
msgid ""
"The monthly payment is calculated so that every period you pay the same "
"amount until the loan is paid off. Total payment is the sum of all those "
"payments (principal + total interest)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:352
msgid "Total Interest and Payoff Date"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:354
msgid ""
"Total interest is the cost of borrowing. A lower rate or shorter term "
"reduces it; a longer term or higher rate increases it. The payoff date is "
"when the balance reaches zero; with extra payments it comes sooner."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:360
msgid ""
"When you enter an extra monthly payment, the calculator applies it to "
"principal only. It then shows how much interest you save and how many months "
"(or years) earlier you pay off the loan compared with the standard schedule."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:366
msgid ""
"The schedule lists each payment (or each year) with the amount going to "
"principal, to interest, and the remaining balance. Early in the loan most of "
"each payment is interest; over time more goes to principal. Use Monthly or "
"Yearly view depending on the detail you need."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/loan_calculator.html:375
