#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/margin_calculator.html:258
msgid "What is the Margin Calculator?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/margin_calculator.html:260
msgid ""
"This calculator helps you work with profit margin and markup. You can find "
"margin and markup from cost and selling price, find the selling price from "
"cost and a desired margin or markup, find cost from price and margin, or "
"convert between margin and markup. Margin is profit as a percentage of "
"selling price; markup is profit as a percentage of cost. The tool includes a "
"comparison table and charts."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/margin_calculator.html:268
msgid ""
"Profit as a percentage of selling price. Margin = (Profit / Price) × 100. "
"Used when you want to know what share of revenue is profit."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/margin_calculator.html:272
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Profit as a percentage of cost. Markup = (Profit / Cost) × 100. Common in "
"retail: e.g. 50%% markup means you add half the cost to set the price."
