#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:183
msgid "What is the Marriage Tax Bonus or Penalty?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:185
msgid ""
"When two people marry, they can file as Married Filing Jointly (MFJ) or "
"Married Filing Separately (MFS). How their combined tax compares to what "
"they would have paid as two single filers is called the marriage bonus (you "
"pay less) or marriage penalty (you pay more). The result depends on your "
"incomes: similar incomes often produce a penalty; very different incomes "
"often produce a bonus, because joint brackets can benefit the higher earner. "
"This calculator uses 2024 federal brackets and standard deductions to "
"estimate the difference."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:193
msgid "Filing as singles vs MFJ"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:194
msgid ""
"Filing as singles: each person's tax if not married. Married Filing Jointly "
"(MFJ): combined income and deductions with one set of brackets (double the "
"single brackets)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:197
msgid "Married Filing Separately (MFS)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:198
msgid ""
"Each spouse files separately; many credits and deductions are limited or "
"lost. In practice, MFJ is usually better when allowed."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:201
msgid "Marriage bonus vs penalty"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/marriage_tax_calculator.html:202
msgid ""
"Marriage bonus: total tax as married is less than combined tax as singles. "
"Marriage penalty: total tax as married is more than combined tax as singles. "
"Similar incomes often produce a penalty; very different incomes often "
"produce a bonus."
msgstr ""

