msgid ""
"The estimated amount you'll pay each month. For repayment mortgages, this "
"covers both capital and interest. For interest-only, it covers interest only "
"— you'll need a separate plan to repay the capital."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_calculator_uk.html:354
msgid ""
"The total amount of interest paid over the full mortgage term. On interest-"
"only mortgages, this figure is significantly higher because the capital "
"never reduces, so you pay interest on the full loan amount for the entire "
"term."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_calculator_uk.html:360
msgid ""
"The total of all payments made over the complete term. For repayment "
"mortgages, this includes the full loan repayment plus interest. For interest-"
"only, this is the total interest plus the capital still owed at the end."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_calculator_uk.html:364
msgid "LTV (Loan-to-Value)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_calculator_uk.html:366
msgid ""
"The ratio of the loan amount to the property's value, expressed as a "
"percentage. Lower LTV means you're borrowing less relative to the property's "
"worth, which typically results in better interest rates from lenders."
msgstr ""

