#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:462
msgid "What is Mortgage Payoff?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:464
msgid ""
"Mortgage payoff refers to paying off your home loan before the end of its "
"original term. By making extra payments — whether monthly, yearly, or as a "
"lump sum — you reduce the principal balance faster, which means less "
"interest accumulates over time. This can save you tens of thousands of "
"dollars and free you from mortgage debt years earlier than planned."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:467
msgid "Total Savings = Original Interest − Payoff Interest"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:470
msgid ""
"The key principle is simple: every extra dollar you pay goes directly toward "
"reducing your principal balance. Since interest is calculated on the "
"remaining balance, a lower balance means less interest on every future "
"payment — creating a compounding savings effect over the life of the loan."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:476
msgid "Payoff Strategies"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:479
msgid "Extra Monthly Payments"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:481
msgid ""
"Adding a fixed amount to your monthly payment is the most common strategy. "
"Even $200-$500 extra per month can save $50,000-$100,000+ in interest and "
"cut 5-10 years off a 30-year mortgage. This method is easy to budget for and "
"provides consistent acceleration."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:485
msgid "Biweekly Payments"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:487
msgid ""
"Instead of 12 monthly payments, you pay half your payment every two weeks. "
"With 52 weeks per year, this results in 26 half-payments — the equivalent of "
"13 full payments instead of 12. That extra payment each year can shave 4-6 "
"years off a 30-year loan with minimal effort."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:491
msgid "Lump Sum Payments"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:493
msgid ""
"One-time payments from bonuses, tax refunds, or inheritance can create a "
"dramatic reduction in your loan balance. A single $10,000 lump sum early in "
"a 30-year mortgage can save over $20,000 in interest. The earlier you make "
"the lump sum, the greater the impact."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:497
msgid "Combined Strategy"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:499
msgid ""
"The most powerful approach combines all strategies: make extra monthly "
"payments, switch to biweekly, and apply windfalls as lump sums. Used "
"together, you could pay off a 30-year mortgage in 15-18 years and save "
"hundreds of thousands in interest."
msgstr ""

