#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:249
msgid "What is a Defined Benefit Pension?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:251
msgid ""
"A defined benefit (DB) pension is a retirement plan where your employer "
"promises a specific monthly or annual benefit at retirement, based on your "
"salary history and years of service. Unlike defined contribution plans (e.g. "
"401(k)), you do not manage the investments; the employer bears the "
"investment risk and guarantees the benefit."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:254
#, python-format
msgid "Annual Pension = Final Salary × Years of Service × Multiplier (%%)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:257
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Common multipliers range from 1.5%% to 2.5%% per year of service. Your final "
"salary is often an average of your last few years of employment."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:263
msgid "Calculator Types"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:268
msgid ""
"Estimate your annual and monthly pension based on final salary, years of "
"service, and a benefit multiplier. Includes COLA (cost of living) projection "
"and present value estimate."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:274
msgid ""
"Compare taking a lump sum payout versus a lifetime annuity. The calculator "
"projects how long the lump sum would last if invested and withdrawn at the "
"same rate as the annuity, and suggests which option may be better for your "
"situation."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:284
msgid ""
"Select the calculator type: Defined Benefit Pension or Lump Sum vs Annuity."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:285
msgid ""
"For Defined Benefit: enter final salary, years of service, multiplier, "
"current age, retirement age, and COLA rate."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:286
msgid ""
"For Lump Sum vs Annuity: enter the monthly annuity offered, the lump sum "
"offered, retirement age, life expectancy, and expected investment return."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:287
msgid "Click 'Calculate Pension' to see your results."
msgstr ""

