msgid "Defined Benefit: Annual & Monthly Pension"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:300
msgid ""
"Your estimated benefit in today's dollars. The replacement ratio is (annual "
"pension ÷ final salary) × 100 and shows what share of your pre-retirement "
"income the pension replaces."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:304
msgid "Total Over 30 Years & Present Value"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:306
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Total benefits assumes 30 years in retirement with COLA applied each year. "
"Present value discounts those future payments to today's dollars at a 4%% "
"rate, giving an equivalent lump-sum value."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:310
msgid "Lump Sum vs Annuity: Recommendation"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:312
msgid ""
"If the lump sum, invested at your expected return and withdrawn at the "
"annuity rate, would still have money left after your life expectancy, the "
"calculator may suggest lump sum. If it would run out sooner, annuity may be "
"better for guaranteed lifetime income."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:325
msgid ""
"A line chart showing your projected annual pension payment each year in "
"retirement. The line rises over time when COLA is applied, so you can see "
"how your benefit grows with inflation."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:331
msgid ""
"Shows the projected balance of the lump sum each year if you invest it and "
"withdraw the same amount as the annuity. If the line falls to zero before "
"your life expectancy, the annuity may provide more security."
msgstr ""

