#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:212
msgid "What is the Rent Affordability Calculator?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:214
#, python-format
msgid ""
"This calculator estimates how much rent you can afford based on your gross "
"monthly income, existing debt payments, and common budgeting rules. It uses "
"the 30%%%% rule (rent should not exceed 30%%%% of gross income), the 28/36 "
"rule, and the 50/30/20 framework to give you a range of affordable rent "
"amounts."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:217
msgid ""
"You enter your income, monthly debt (car, loans, credit cards), estimated "
"utilities, and a preferred rent percentage. The result shows recommended "
"rent, budget breakdown, and rent by different guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:222
msgid "Key Rules"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:224
#, python-format
msgid "30%% Rule"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:225
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Rent should not exceed 30%% of your gross monthly income. This is the most "
"common guideline for rent affordability."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:228
msgid "28/36 Rule"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:229
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Housing (rent + utilities) should not exceed 28%% of gross income; total "
"debt (housing + other debts) should not exceed 36%%."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:232
msgid "50/30/20 Rule"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:233
#, python-format
msgid ""
"50%% of take-home pay for needs (rent, utilities, food), 30%% for wants, "
"20%% for savings. Rent is part of the 50%% needs bucket."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:241
msgid "Gross income"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:242
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Income before taxes. The 30%% rule uses gross (not take-home) income for "
"consistency with how landlords often qualify tenants."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:245
msgid "Monthly obligations"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:246
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Car payments, student loans, credit card minimums, and other debt. Higher "
"debt reduces how much you can safely put toward rent under the 36%% rule."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:249
msgid "After rent"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rent_calculator.html:250
msgid ""
"Estimated remaining after rent, utilities, and debt. This is for food, "
"savings, and other expenses; a positive number is essential."
msgstr ""

