#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:184
msgid ""
"The Rental Property Calculator estimates key investment metrics for a rental "
"property: Net Operating Income (NOI), cap rate, gross yield, and cash flow "
"after operating expenses and optional mortgage payments. It helps you "
"compare properties, screen deals, and understand how much income a rental "
"can generate before and after financing."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:187
msgid ""
"All results are based on the numbers you enter. Use realistic rent, "
"expenses, and vacancy so the metrics reflect true potential. Operating "
"expenses typically include property tax, insurance, maintenance, utilities, "
"property management, and repairs—but not the mortgage."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:196
msgid "Cap Rate (Capitalization Rate)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:198
msgid ""
"NOI ÷ Property Price. Measures the property’s return as if you paid cash (no "
"loan). Higher cap rate usually means higher yield but often higher risk or "
"lower appreciation. Use it to compare similar properties in the same market."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:202
msgid "NOI (Net Operating Income)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:204
msgid ""
"Effective rental income minus all operating expenses. It does not include "
"mortgage payments. Lenders and investors use NOI to assess whether the "
"property can support debt and generate income."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:210
msgid ""
"Gross annual rent ÷ Property Price. A simple ratio before vacancy and "
"expenses. Useful for a quick first look; cap rate and cash flow are better "
"for real decisions."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:216
msgid ""
"NOI minus annual mortgage payments. This is the cash you keep each year "
"after paying the loan. Positive cash flow improves sustainability; negative "
"cash flow may be acceptable only if you expect strong appreciation or tax "
"benefits."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:226
msgid "Enter the property purchase price or current market value."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:227
msgid "Enter expected monthly rental income (market rent)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:228
msgid ""
"Enter total monthly operating expenses (tax, insurance, maintenance, "
"utilities, management, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:229
#, python-format
msgid "Set a vacancy rate (e.g. 5–10%%) to account for empty periods."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:230
msgid ""
"If you have or plan a mortgage, enter the monthly payment to see cash flow "
"after debt."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:231
msgid ""
"Click Calculate to see cap rate, NOI, cash flow, and the Income vs Expenses "
"chart."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:242
msgid ""
"The amount of cash left each year after all income, operating expenses, and "
"mortgage payments. Shown as both annual and monthly. This is what you can "
"use for savings, reinvestment, or living expenses."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:248
msgid ""
"Gross annual rent reduced by your vacancy rate. It represents the income you "
"can realistically expect after accounting for empty months."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:252
msgid "Cap Rate & Gross Yield"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:254
msgid ""
"Cap rate uses NOI (after expenses); gross yield uses gross rent (before "
"expenses). Cap rate is the standard for comparing rental investments. Gross "
"yield is a quick screening tool."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:264
msgid ""
"The Income vs Expenses bar chart shows four annual amounts: Effective Income "
"(rent after vacancy), Operating Expenses (shown as a negative bar), Mortgage "
"(debt service, also negative if entered), and Net Cash Flow. Positive bars "
"are income or profit; negative bars are costs. Net Cash Flow is what remains "
"after all outflows."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:273
msgid "Effective Gross Income"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:274
msgid "Gross Annual Rent × (1 − Vacancy Rate ÷ 100)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:278
msgid "Effective Gross Income − Annual Operating Expenses"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:282
msgid "NOI ÷ Property Price × 100"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:286
msgid "NOI − (Monthly Mortgage × 12)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:297
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Effective income is reduced by the vacancy rate. Use realistic expense and "
"vacancy assumptions (e.g. 5–10%% vacancy, full operating costs)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rental_property_calculator.html:301
msgid ""
"This calculator is for estimation and education only. It does not include "
