"bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly, and annual amounts. It also lets you "
"calculate salary raises (percentage or fixed amount), compare two job offers "
"on an annual basis, and compute overtime pay for a given week. All "
"conversions use the hours per week and weeks per year you enter (default 40 "
"and 52)."
