"62 (with a reduction) or delay up to 70 (with an increase). Your Full "
"Retirement Age (FRA) is when you get 100%%%% of your Primary Insurance "
"Amount (PIA)—it's between 66 and 67 depending on your birth year."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:216
msgid "Full Retirement Age (FRA)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:217
#, python-format
msgid ""
"66–67 depending on birth year. At FRA you receive 100%% of your PIA. Born "
"1960 or later: FRA is 67."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:220
msgid "Early (62) vs Delayed (70)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:221
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Claiming at 62 reduces benefits by about 6.7%% per year before FRA. Delaying "
"past FRA increases benefits by 8%% per year up to age 70."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:224
msgid "AIME & PIA"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:225
msgid ""
"Average Indexed Monthly Earnings (AIME) is based on your highest 35 years of "
"earnings. Primary Insurance Amount (PIA) is the benefit at FRA, calculated "
"from AIME using bend points."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:232
msgid "Enter your birth year and month (determines FRA)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:233
msgid "Enter current annual earnings and years worked (used to estimate AIME)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:234
msgid "Select your planned retirement/claiming age (62–70)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:235
msgid ""
"Click Calculate to see estimated monthly benefit, PIA, and comparison by age."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:239
msgid "Understanding the Charts & Table"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:240
msgid ""
"The bar chart shows your estimated monthly benefit at each claiming age from "
"62 to 70. Your planned age is highlighted in blue, FRA in green. The table "
"and lifetime comparison show the same data in different forms; the break-"
"even age tells you when delaying to 70 would exceed total benefits from "
"claiming at 62."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:243
msgid "Formulas (simplified)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:244
#, python-format
msgid ""
"PIA uses bend points: 90%% of first segment, 32%% of second, 15%% of third. "
"Early reduction: 5/9 of 1%% per month for first 36 months, then 5/12 of 1%% "
"per month. Delayed credit: 2/3 of 1%% per month (8%% per year) after FRA up "
"to 70."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:251
msgid ""
"Estimates are based on current earnings and simplified rules. Actual "
"benefits depend on your complete earnings history and the law in effect at "
"claiming."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/social_security_calculator.html:255
msgid ""
