msgid ""
"A VA loan is a mortgage guaranteed by the U.S. Department of Veterans "
"Affairs. It is available to eligible veterans, active-duty service members, "
"and qualifying surviving spouses. VA loans are issued by private lenders but "
"backed by the federal government, which allows lenders to offer favorable "
"terms such as no down payment and no private mortgage insurance (PMI)."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:301
msgid ""
"The VA does not lend money directly; it provides a guarantee that protects "
"the lender if the borrower defaults. This guarantee enables lenders to offer "
"competitive interest rates and flexible qualification requirements. The VA "
"funding fee helps sustain the program and can be paid at closing or financed "
"into the loan amount."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:310
msgid "No Down Payment"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:311
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Qualified borrowers can finance up to 100%% of the home's value. No down "
"payment is required, though you may choose to put money down to reduce the "
"loan amount and funding fee."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:315
msgid ""
"Unlike conventional loans, VA loans do not require Private Mortgage "
"Insurance (PMI), even with zero down. This can save hundreds of dollars per "
"month compared to other loan types."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:318
msgid "Competitive Rates &amp; Limited Closing Costs"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:319
msgid ""
"Lenders often offer competitive interest rates on VA loans. VA also limits "
"certain closing costs that lenders can charge to veterans."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:322
msgid "No Prepayment Penalties &amp; Assumable Loans"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:323
msgid ""
"You can pay off your VA loan early without penalty. VA loans are also "
"assumable, meaning a qualified buyer can take over your loan and its terms."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/va_mortgage_calculator.html:332
msgid ""
"The VA funding fee is a one-time fee that helps offset the cost of the "
"program to taxpayers. The fee is based on your down payment (or equity), "
"whether it's your first VA loan or a subsequent use, and whether you're in "
"the regular military or Reserves/National Guard. Veterans with service-"
"connected disabilities may be exempt from the funding fee. The fee can be "
"paid at closing or financed into the loan."
msgstr ""

