#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:161
msgid "What is VAT?"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:163
msgid ""
"VAT (Value Added Tax) is a consumption tax added at each stage of production "
"or distribution. It is used in over 160 countries. GST (Goods and Services "
"Tax) is similar and used in Australia, Canada, India, and others. This "
"calculator lets you add VAT to a net price, remove VAT from a gross price, "
"or find the VAT amount from either."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:166
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Gross = Net × (1 + VAT%%) &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; Net = Gross ÷ (1 + "
"VAT%%) &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; VAT = Gross − Net"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:174
msgid "Add VAT (Net → Gross)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:175
msgid ""
"You have a price excluding VAT; the calculator adds VAT to get the price "
"including VAT."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:178
msgid "Remove VAT (Gross → Net)"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:179
msgid ""
"You have a price including VAT; the calculator extracts the net amount and "
"VAT."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:182
msgid "VAT from Net / VAT from Gross"
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:183
msgid ""
"From a net amount you get VAT only (and gross); from a gross amount you get "
"the VAT portion and net."
msgstr ""

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/vat_calculator.html:191
msgid ""
