#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:152
msgid "How to Measure Your Bra Size at Home"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:153
msgid ""
"Your bra size consists of two parts: the band size (a number) and the cup "
"size (a letter). The band size is your underbust measurement rounded to the "
"nearest even number. The cup size is determined by the difference between "
"your bust and band measurements. Getting accurate measurements is the first "
"step to finding a comfortable, well-fitting bra."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:154
msgid "Bra Size = Band Size (number) + Cup Size (letter)"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:157
msgid "Step-by-Step Measurement Instructions"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:159
msgid "1. Measure Your Underbust (Ribcage)"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:159
msgid ""
"Wrap a measuring tape snugly around your ribcage, directly under your bust. "
"Keep the tape level and parallel to the ground. This measurement determines "
"your band size."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:160
msgid "2. Measure Your Bust (Fullest Point)"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:160
msgid ""
"Wrap the tape around the fullest part of your bust, typically at nipple "
"level. Keep the tape level and not too tight. Wear a non-padded bra for the "
"most accurate measurement."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:161
msgid "3. Enter Measurements & Calculate"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:161
