msgid "Sizing Systems Explained: US vs UK vs EU vs FR"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:175
msgid "US / CA / MX Sizing"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:175
msgid ""
"Band sizes 28-50. Cup progression: AA, A, B, C, D, DD, DDD, G, H, I, J, K, "
"L, M, N. Most common in North America."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:176
msgid "UK / PK / IN / NZ / AU / ZA Sizing"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:176
msgid ""
"Same band sizes. Different cup progression after D: DD, E, F, FF, G, GG, H, "
"HH, J, JJ. Widely used in Commonwealth countries."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:177
msgid "EU / IT / ES / DE / JP / CN / BR Sizing"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:177
msgid ""
"Same band sizes as US. Cups: AA, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, M, N. "
"Alphabetical progression."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:178
msgid "FR (France) Sizing"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:178
msgid ""
"Uses centimeter-based band sizes (add 15 to US/UK band). Cups same as EU. "
"Example: US 34C = FR 49C."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:182
msgid "What Are Sister Sizes?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:183
msgid ""
"Sister sizes are bra sizes that share the same cup volume but have different "
"band and cup letter combinations. For example, 34C, 32D, and 36B are all "
"sister sizes — they hold the same amount of breast tissue but distribute "
"support differently."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:185
msgid "Example: Sister sizes of 34C"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:196
msgid "Bra Fitting Tips"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:198
msgid ""
"Wear a non-padded, well-fitting bra when measuring for the most accurate "
"results."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:199
msgid ""
"Sizes can vary between brands. Always try on when possible, and consider "
"sister sizes."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:200
msgid ""
"The band should be snug and level around your torso. You should be able to "
"fit two fingers under it."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:201
msgid "The center gore (front panel) should sit flat against your chest."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:202
msgid ""
"If you're between sizes, go up a band size and down a cup size (or vice "
"versa) using sister sizes."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:208
msgid "How do I measure my bra size at home?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:208
msgid ""
"Measure your underbust snugly around your ribcage, then measure your bust at "
"the fullest point. Enter both measurements into our calculator to get your "
"size instantly."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:209
msgid "What are sister sizes and when should I use them?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:209
msgid ""
"Sister sizes have the same cup volume but different band/cup combinations. "
"Use them when your regular size isn't available or when a band feels too "
"tight/loose."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:210
msgid "How do US and UK bra sizes differ?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:210
msgid ""
"Band sizes are the same, but cup progressions differ after D. US: DD, DDD, "
"G, H. UK: DD, E, F, FF, G, GG. Use our converter for accurate conversions."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:211
msgid "Why does my bra size vary between brands?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:211
msgid ""
"Different brands use different fit standards and materials. Always try on "
"bras when possible. Sister sizes can help you find a fit in brands that run "
"differently."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:212
msgid "Should I measure with or without a bra?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bra_size_calculator.html:212
msgid ""
"Wear a non-padded, well-fitting bra for the most accurate measurement. The "
"bra should not add extra volume."
msgstr ""

