#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:460
msgid "How accurate are the conversions?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:461
msgid ""
"All conversions use internationally recognized conversion factors and are "
"computed using high-precision numerical libraries. Results are "
"scientifically accurate for educational and practical use."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:464
msgid "Why is temperature conversion different from other conversions?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:465
msgid ""
"Most unit conversions use simple multiplication factors. Temperature scales "
"(Celsius, Fahrenheit, Kelvin, Rankine) use offset-based formulas because "
"their zero points differ. For example, °F = (°C × 9/5) + 32 involves both "
"multiplication and addition."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:468
msgid "What is the difference between KB and KiB?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:469
msgid ""
"KB (Kilobyte) uses the SI standard where 1 KB = 1,000 bytes. KiB (Kibibyte) "
"uses the binary standard where 1 KiB = 1,024 bytes. The binary prefixes (Ki, "
"Mi, Gi) were introduced by the IEC to remove ambiguity in digital storage "
"measurements."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:472
msgid "Can I convert between categories?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:473
msgid ""
"No, conversions are only possible within the same category. For example, you "
"can convert meters to feet (both length), but not meters to kilograms "
"(length vs. weight). Select a category first, then choose units within it."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:476
msgid "How does the swap button work?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:477
msgid ""
"The swap button (↕) exchanges the 'From' and 'To' units instantly. This is "
"useful when you want to perform the reverse conversion without manually "
"reselecting units."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:480
msgid "What units are supported?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/conversion_calculator.html:481
