#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/density_calculator.html:221
msgid "What is Density?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/density_calculator.html:222
msgid ""
"Density is a physical property that measures the mass per unit volume of a "
"substance. It tells you how tightly packed the matter is in a given space. "
"The formula is simple: Density = Mass ÷ Volume (ρ = m / V). Different "
"materials have different densities — water is 1,000 kg/m³, aluminum is 2,700 "
"kg/m³, and gold is 19,300 kg/m³."
msgstr ""

