#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/horsepower_calculator.html:194
msgid "Why 5252?"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/horsepower_calculator.html:195
msgid ""
"The constant 5252 comes from unit conversions. One horsepower is 550 ft-lb "
"per second. To go from RPM to radians per minute: (550 × 60) / (2π) ≈ 5252. "
"This means horsepower and torque curves always cross at 5252 RPM when "
"plotted on the same graph."
msgstr ""

