#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/weight_calculator.html:215
msgid "What is Weight? Understanding Weight vs Mass"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/weight_calculator.html:216
msgid ""
"Weight is the gravitational force exerted on an object. When you step on a "
"scale and see kilograms or pounds, you are measuring how strongly gravity "
"pulls on your body. Unlike mass — which is the actual amount of matter and "
"stays the same everywhere — your weight changes depending on your location. "
"For example, you would weigh about one-sixth on the Moon compared to Earth "
"because the Moon's gravity is weaker."
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/weight_calculator.html:217
msgid "Weight = Mass × Gravity (W = m × g)"
msgstr ""

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/weight_calculator.html:218
msgid ""
"Use our weight calculator above to convert between kilograms and pounds, "
"find out how much you would weigh on Mars or Jupiter, or calculate mass from "
"weight using the physics formula. All results include detailed step-by-step "
"solutions."
